WTP: ChangeLog
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[v%%VERSION] <%%EMAIL> ( %%DATE )
  * Fixed a bug in the path and filename handling.

[v1.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Sun May  2 15:43:30 CEST 2004 )
  * Fixes in error reporting.
  * Tests with win32 FTP server (UNIX type). Works.
  * Added a 'Change dir' button to the dir input box for clarity.
  * Comments fixed in source.
  * Fixes in the setup script.
  
[v0.7.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Mon Jan 26 23:31:18 CET 2004 )
  * register_global=off Compatible.
  * Rewrote authorization / login / ftp connect stuff.
  * Minor code-cleanups.
  * Rewrote most parts of sorting. USort functions are now cleaner and 
    faster. Sorting directions are correct. Sorting another column will
    not alternate the sort direction. (i.e: current sort is "filename-ASC". 
    Click date and sort will become "date-DESC". Should be: "date-ASC".
  * Fixed numerous warnings.
  * FTP servers on different ports are now supported.
  * Anonymous FTP supported.
  * Univeral Error() function.
  * Better error checking all over (just about all ftp_* functions).
  * Most icons now have onMouseOver information.
  
[v0.6.3] <%%EMAIL> ( Mon Nov 10 19:45:30 CET 2003 )
  * Non-file lines in the rawlist returned by the ftp server are now ignored.
  * Bugfix for incorrect pop-up sizes.
  * Hidden files can now be shown or hidden (default). Setting is rembered during
    session.
  * Directories are now always at the top of the list.

[v0.6.2] <%%EMAIL> ( Thu Sep  4 17:23:10 CEST 2003 )
  * Fixed a bug where you couldn't log in if only one hostname was specified.
  * Fixed a bug where downloads wouldn't work in new PHP versions due to wrong FTP URL.

[v0.6.1] <%%EMAIL> ( Sat Jun  7 02:20:38 CEST 2003 )
  * Added confirmation dialogs to the delete operations (only direct delete
    icons, not the explicit select files & delete button action)
  * Added tooltips (mousecursor hover) to the icons.

[v0.6.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Sat Apr 19 13:33:21 CEST 2003 )
  * Implemented sorting on various column headers.
  * Directories are now deleted recursively.

[v0.5.3] <%%EMAIL> ( Sat Mar 22 13:40:54 CET 2003 )
  * Created a document containing testcases. Only useful for developers. You
    can find it under docs/developer/testcases.txt
  * Fixed the time-out username bug. When the session would time-out, the 
    login box would be displayed again, but the username entry would be filled
    with the previous directory. Now you will be returned to the correct 
    directory after logging in again.
  * Fixed numerous bugs in weird dir and filenames (containing &, +, etc)
  * Added 'About WTP' information to help screen, including a GPL notice and 
    links to the homepage.

[v0.5.2] <%%EMAIL> ( Thu Mar 13 23:08:51 CET 2003 )
  * Fixed multiple errors with wrongly passed file and dirnames. More errors
    are present, but these were the most important to address.

[v0.5.1] <%%EMAIL> ( Sun Feb 16 00:04:56 CET 2003 )
  * Fixed bug in the bookmark selector on the button bar. 

[v0.5.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Mon Jan 27 13:50:57 CET 2003 )
  * Lines read from the ftp server's LIST output with less than 12 columns
    are now ignored. This adds compatibility with MicroBSD 6.5 FTP server)
  * WTP can now be configured to allow access to a list of hosts
  * It is now possible to move a file or set of files.
  * The bookmarks filename separator has changed from '-' to ' '. (space)
  * Changed the default preferences path from /usr/local/wtp to /var/wtp.

[v0.4.1] <%%EMAIL> ( Sat Jan  4 16:05:47 CET 2003 )
  * Fixed repeated display of hidden form fields in DirList display.
  * A dir can be specified before log-in. After logging in, the user will
    be taken to this dir automatically.
  
[v0.4.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Sat Dec 28 17:19:53 CET 2002 )
  * Added a help screen.
  * 'Current dir' path's can now be clicked, so you can move to them quick
  * Numbers are now seperated with ',' each thousands
  * Added file selection & deletion support.
  * Fixed double display of html headers in DirList

[v0.3.1] <%%EMAIL> ( ? )
  * IE SSL download bug fixed. This was not a WTP bug, but a IE/apache-ssl bug.
    Please read section 'Installing' in the README for information on how to 
    fix this bug. (closes bug #2);
  I Think I forgot to release this version?

[v0.3.0] <%%EMAIL> ( ?  )
  * Bookmark support added. Everything now needs a code cleanup. Thank you 
    late-night-coding ;)
  * The way the current dir is displayed has been made better readable.
  * Temporarily removed the useless File/Dir move icon until move has been implemented.
  * Created an installation script.
  * Fixed the '+' download bug (bug-id 1)

[v0.2.3] <%%EMAIL> ( Fri May 10 13:30:09 CEST 2002 )
  * Added a 'WTP' text in the buttonbar.

[v0.2.2] <%%EMAIL> ( Fri May 10 13:30:09 CEST 2002 )
  * Fixed the toolbar background for IE.
  * Fixed monospaced fonts for IE.

[v0.2.1] <%%EMAIL> ( Tue May  7 20:52:04 CEST 2002 )
  * Fixed the spaces between month/day/year.

[v0.2.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Sun May  5 14:05:32 CEST 2002 )
  * Better error checking at login
  * Pop-ups with error messages at login
  * Prefill of login boxes on error
  * Downloaded files are now named correctly 
  * Fixed the need to shift-click download files.
  * Added header which sends files size at download.
  * Added refresh option
  * Correct handling of files with '+'. Closes bug #1
  * Correct(er) handling of symlinks.
  * Login information is now stored in session instead of cookies.

[v0.1.0] <%%EMAIL> ( Sun May  5 14:05:32 CEST 2002 )
  * Initial release.
